               <p>I am a <rs id="t17780429-83-viclabel390" type="occupation">victualler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17780429-83-victim708 t17780429-83-viclabel390"></join>; the prisoner drawed beer for me; the handkerchief was missed out of a drawer in the kitchen, and found tied round the prisoner's middle under his shirt.</p>

               <p>(The handkerchief was produced in court and deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17780429-83-person710">
                  JOHN
                   GREGG
               <interp inst="t17780429-83-person710" type="surname" value="GREGG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-83-person710" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-83-person710" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>

               <p>Mrs. Powell missed the handkerchief, and suspecting the prisoner, desired me to search him; I did and found it tied round his middle, under his shirt.</p>

               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>

               <p>I had a disorder upon me, and therefore I tied the handkerchief round my middle; I had no intention to steal it.</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t17780429-83-verdict391" type="verdictDescription">
